{"questionId":"10991","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Ethyne, C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub>, reacts with oxygen in welding torches.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Ethyne reacts with steam.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub> (g) + H<sub>2</sub>O (g) → C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>O (g)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Two possible products are:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/5f1011b29505261590600595b648a581feb2c530.png\" width=\"317\" height=\"189\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Product<strong> A</strong> contains a carbon–carbon double bond. State the type of reactions that compounds containing this bond are likely to undergo.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«electrophilic» addition/A<sub>«E»</sub>&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Accept “polymerization”.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10991","referenceCode":"19M.2.sl.TZ2.1c(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Product A contains a carbon–carbon double bond. State the type of reactions that compounds containing this bond are likely to undergo.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}